     <h4>Bank Zachodni WBK – a good place for your professional career </h4>
<p>
The workshops organised by Bank Zachodni WBK will cover mock interviews with volunteers. Those of you who decide to take part in the workshop will first receive written information about the task, the time needed for preparation and its completion. 
</p>
<p>
The interviews will help us to identify and jointly discuss our expectations from candidates, the skills we are looking for and the factors which make us select a specific person for a given job.
</p><p>
The banking industry is a perfect place for people with different educational backgrounds – it is a good place to start a career for people having a degree in economy, management, mathematics, psychology, marketing, legal studies or other fields. The most important thing to us is your skills and qualifications.
</p><p>
Each person taking part in a mock interview will be provided with feedback at a pre-agreed time after the workshop. The received comments will help you to identify your strengths and weaknesses for your future job seeking purposes. During the feedback session, you will also have an opportunity to learn how to plan your professional development to be more competitive on the job market. 
</p><p>
Workshop will be run by Beata Pietrzykowska-Stachnik - Head of the Recruitment and Outplacement in Bank Zachodni WBK. 
</p><h4>
Please feel invited to our workshop!</h4>
